CNA Financial Corporation Key Developments

CNA Appoints Robert Thomas as Senior Vice President, Claim Analytics, Finance and Operations
Jul 12 17
CNA announced the appointment of Robert Thomas to fill the newly created position of Senior Vice President, Claim Analytics, Finance and Operations within the company's Worldwide P&C Claim organization. In this role, Thomas will be responsible for all aspects of CNA's Claim Analytics, Finance and Operations areas, including working closely with the company's Commercial, Specialty and International businesses and corporate functions.  He will report to Andrew Pinkes, Executive Vice President, Worldwide P&C Claim.


CNA Appoints Gregg Fergot as Vice President, Underwriting, Technology Segment
Jun 27 17
CNA announced the appointment of Gregg Fergot as Vice President, Underwriting, leading the Company's Technology Segment. In this role, Fergot will be responsible for leading the Technology Segment in implementing its strategic and operational objectives. He will be based in San Francisco and report to Dieter Korte, Senior Vice President, Customer Segments. Fergot joins CNA with more than 25 years of business experience in the technology underwriting field. Most recently, he served as Vice President, Head of Technology, Middle Market Commercial, for Zurich. Prior to that role, he served as Western Zone Vice President, Global Technology for Travelers; Regional Manager, Technology Underwriting for Chubb; and various technology underwriting roles.


CNA Financial Corporation Appoints Scott Weber as Executive Vice President and General Counsel
Jun 2 17
CNA Financial Corporation announced the appointment of Scott Weber to Executive Vice President and General Counsel. In this role, Weber will serve as a principal counsel to the CEO, senior management team and board of directors. He will lead the Law Department, which is responsible for the company's legal affairs, compliance, regulatory and government affairs, corporate affairs, securities and litigation, as well as providing legal support for the company's business operations. He will report to Dino E. Robusto, Chairman and Chief Executive Officer, the company. Prior to joining the company earlier this year, Weber most recently served as a Managing Director for Stroz Friedberg.


